From: Aishwarya R <aisr@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 17 Jul 2025 14:46:35 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 3/7] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:HOSTAPD: Add hostapd_cli support for 
 setting DSCP policies

Introduce a new hostapd_cli command SET_DSCP_POLICY to allow
runtime configuration of DSCP policies for connected stations via the
hostapd CLI.

Parsing logic for DSCP policy parameters including DSCP value,
classifier mask, IP version, IP addresses, ports, and domain name.
Add Support for both IPv4 and IPv6 classifiers.
Add support to validate input parameters and construction of frame
classifiers

Below is the example set_dscp_policy cli command

hostapd_cli -i phy00.1-0 set_dscp_policy <sta_addr> policy_id=1
request_type=Add dscp=46 classifier_mask=0x55 ip_version=4
dst_ip=192.165.100.7 dst_port=5201 protocol=17

Patch-dependency:none
Tag: DAP

Signed-off-by: Aishwarya R <aisr@qti.qualcomm.com>
